title: Sutherland Brothers & Quiver - Beat Of The Street (1974) MP3
description: The Sutherland Brothers (Gavin and Iain Sutherland) originally performed as a folk and rock music duo in the British music scene in the early 1970s, and then from 1973 to 1978 joined with rock band Quiver to record and tour as Sutherland Brothers & Quiver. Under this combined moniker, the group recorded several albums and had a significant international hit single with the song "Arms of Mary" in 1976. In North America they are primarily known for their 1973 debut single "I Don't Want To Love You ( But You Got Me Anyway)", which was not a hit in the UK
